2014 PRE Gelding Available for your consideration, just in time for the holidays! 🎁 Val has been in my training program for about three months now and he has been an absolute pleasure to bring along for his owner. 💫 Val is now available and looking for his next partner! He is an 8 yr old PRE Gelding and stands 16.1h. Imported from Spain in 2019. Amateur friendly, easy going temperament, smooth gaits. He’s happily progressing quickly in his training, currently schooling all of third level with a green flying change and showing great ability for the collected work. Val is easy to get along with, well mannered, loves attention, no history of major illness or injury, no bad vices. Previously shown working equitation as well. New video coming this week!

Located 30 min North of San Diego Airport 

Message me for more details or email me at donadtdressage@gmail.com

📸 @evangrooms

⭐️1000th post⭐️ For my 1000th post I’m going with a throwback photo to the first time I ever saw Ashley @donadt_dressage compete in dressage. Almost 10 years ago!

I fell in love with the girl who loved horses and the sport of dressage! Her dedication and lifelong passion for horses has always been incredibly inspiring to me and it’s been my goal since day one to always support that however I could. 

I just never would have realized then that 7 years later one of those ways would be working alongside Ashley at her training program Donadt Dressage as a horse groom. And loving the horses as well and observing their every movement and thought so I can make goofy Horses & Humor content for the horse world and for those outside of the horse world too! I am just grateful to have learned all things horses through Ashley who loves and cares for each and every horse in her life with 100% of her heart!

And thank you to all of our followers who watch my videos, who follow Ashley’s journey in dressage on @donadt_dressage , who like and comment and share all of our posts. Creating content and building an audience has supported us in ways we would have never realized. Your overwhelming positivity on all our posts has touched us deeply and we only strive to return the positivity and love back in our posts, through our love of horses 🙏❤️

At Donadt Dressage, we are always seeking learning opportunities and ways to have fun, build community, and become better partners for our horses. So earlier this week, it was a pleasure to host a two day clinic with Lientje Schuler! 😀

Based in Germany, Lientje has worked as a rider for Isabell Werth the past year and a half, and prior to that she was assistant trainer to Steffen and Shannon Peters for 11 years. She is a CDI Grand Prix rider and US National Young Horse Champion. 

Thank you so much Lientje for an amazing two days, filled with lots of smiles and learning! ❤️ @lientje3 

So proud of my students and their horses for always showing up to be the best that they can be for their partners. Excited to work on our homework for next time. 📝🐴🥰

Photos by the amazing @evangrooms 🤩

Who is looking for their 17.3h Unicorn!? 🦄 Meet Sully - a true gem of an amateur horse, looking for his forever dressage and trail partner. SAFE SAFE SAFE. 

15 yr old (2008) 17.3h Oldenburg Gelding (San Schufro x Rubinstein)

Amateur and beginner friendly!! Super steady, tolerant, and forgiving. More whoa than go. Previously trained/shown to PSG, he loves being a teacher and confidence builder for beginner or timid riders, or those new to dressage. Great for lunge lessons. He also loves going on hacks and trail rides, alone or with other horses.

He’s had a five star owner in a full time training program with me for the past two years, and has been ridden by his amateur owner and lease riders from Intro to Third Level. 

Good home super important. Normal maintenance for a horse his age as well as a 4yr old knee injury that is only cosmetic. Priced accordingly. X-rays on file from PPE in 2021. Please message me for more info!

📍Located 30 min from San Diego International Airport. 

📸 @evangrooms

🌟 We are hiring! 🌟 Come join our
team with FEI Dressage Trainer, Ashley Donadt and her husband/groom @evangrooms !

We are looking for a new member of the team as a full time groom. This is a paid, full time position, based in📍Rancho Santa Fe, CA. More details below, and if you are interested please submit our application form/questionnaire (link in bio). We look forward to hearing from you! 😀

🔹 We are seeking qualified applicants who are hardworking, self motivated and willing to work independently as well as in a team environment. 
🔹Looking for a dedicated person who loves horses to help care for our horses in training. We enjoy our work and the horses are our top priority. 
🔹Candidates must have experience with horses, plus a cooperative and positive attitude.

🔸This position includes:
6 days/week 
1 day off/week 
7am-4pm (with lunch break)
10 horses shared with another full time groom
Tacking
Grooming
Bathing horses
Some stall cleaning
Turning out horses
Hand walking/Eurocisor
Feeding horses
Cleaning the barn
Cleaning tack
Laundry

Horse show recap! ➡️ It was so fun to be back at our local, recently re-opened, Del Mar Horse Park! @hits_delmar 👏🤩

Really proud of our team! Junior rider @camerondressage and his lovely mare, Rosie, rode 3-3 for the first time, earning a 68%! Love seeing this partnership grow! 🌹😍

@colleenjkinninger and Cayenne earned a PB at PSG and a qualifying score towards their USDF Silver Medal! 💪🙌💛

My mare, Keira, dipped her toes in Second Level for the first time, and got a 63%! After showing First level test 2 the first day for a 62%! I’m really happy she put in two steady tests both days. She tried so hard for me and kept her focus in the busy atmosphere. She can be a handful to say the least, and always keeps me on my toes, but I’m so happy that her trust in me and the training is starting to pay off. 🐴🥰

It was extra special because my mom (who bred Keira out of my childhood thoroughbred mare, Keela) was able to come into town for the show from WA state. Also fun to have our friends and other barn family come visit at the show too! @julie_hauck @jesskastewart @kelseytheherbalist @ellison_wang @mperreault27 

Thank you to everyone who helped make this happen, and to CDS SD Chapter for an amazing show complete with the entertaining “International” Party on Friday night! (We celebrated Oktoberfest in July! 🙃🍻) @elliedressage @shirleylongrogozienski @carlahayes6493

I got to go watch the second day of the Ingrid Klimke Masterclass this past weekend, and there were so many great nuggets of wisdom! 🤩 Her love for the horses was so clear, and her dedication to the classical training principles is so inspiring!

This has been a popular topic amongst my students in training lately, and it was so refreshing to hear the reminder from Ingrid as well - WE ALL MAKE MISTAKES. IT’S OK! Don’t be afraid of the mistakes. EMBRACE them. I loved how Ingrid went on to encourage us to change our way of thinking about “mistakes”, by recognizing instead that “it’s a moment where the horse tried, and just gave the wrong answer”. I thought this was a beautiful way of thinking about it. 

I encourage my students that it’s ok to make a mistake because I want them to be comfortable enough to experiment and use their own feel in front me. It’s the same for the horses. It shows me you’re trying! When you try to cover up or prevent a mistake from happening, you’re likely over riding which is going to lead to more tension and frustration. By allowing mistakes, it shows me what’s truly going on between horse and rider, and that we’re getting somewhere by pushing out of the comfort zone. Of course we don’t want to push too far into the panic zone, so then we slow down and take the time to explain what’s happening to develop a better understanding.

✨ “Mistakes” are where the learning happens. ✨

📷 @evangrooms

I thought it was time to share a little update on what Liberty and I have been up to! As life with horses goes, it has been a rollercoaster of a ride.🎢 So I wanted to take a moment to give a little more background into our story, as we’re also turning the page into a new chapter together. 😍

Liberty holds a very special place in my heart. I believe there are many once in a lifetime horses, and she is definitely one of mine. I’m forever grateful to have had the ride on her in 2022, with the support of my wonderful clients who owned her then. We worked our way through small tour with an eye on earning an invitation to the USEF Festival of Champions. I learned so much through that whole season with her. We finished the season 14th on the USEF Intermediate 1 ranking list, when she unfortunately had an injury that would not allow us to travel and compete at Nationals. It’s been a roller coaster ever since, with the reoccurring injury keeping us on the sidelines time after time. As disappointing as that was, I’m more grateful to still have our partnership and the biggest gift of all to still have her in my life. 

We’re so happy to say she is a forever part of our family now. @evangrooms and I look forward to the future with her, and to give her the best life we can after everything she’s given us. She has so much heart, love of life, and a work ethic like no other, so given her new downtime,  we’ve decided to shift focus, and are now looking at sharing her qualities through breeding. We tried this past summer, but after two unsuccessful attempts, we are taking the winter off, and will try again next season. I can’t wait to share this journey more with you all! 🤞🏼🍀🦄

While we didn’t get to continue our training to Grand Prix, the goal of dancing and riding in the big tour still remains. They say if plans don’t work, change the plan but never the goal. So now I’m dreaming of a baby Liberty dancing their way to GP one day! 🤩
